Science Fiction Novels and Spoilers
[Science fiction novels] are an exercise in thinking, "What could happen if these possibilities are possible" or "What could happen if these assumptions are made?" but it clashes with the idea that "[spoilers] are not good," and you can't write "I see, if these assumptions are made, this could happen! I can't write "I see, this is what happens when you have this kind of premise! What a waste.

